EDFROMNJ@DELPHI.COM (edfromnj@news.delphi.com) wrote:
> My question is - could a quantum computer be simulated in software?


To simulate a quantum computer with a classical computer takes 
non polynomially large time.

In general the time required would be proportional to 2^n
where n is the number of quantum bits.

